sequenceDiagram
    participant Admin as Platform Admin
    participant API as Kubernetes API Server<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant Webhook as Webhook Server<br/>9443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant DSCCtrl as DSC Controller
    participant CompCtrl as Component Controllers
    participant K8s as Kubernetes Resources

    Note over Admin,K8s: Flow 1: DataScienceCluster Creation

    Admin->>API: POST DataScienceCluster CR<br/>Auth: User credentials
    API->>Webhook: POST /validate/dsc<br/>mTLS (K8s API Server cert)
    Webhook->>API: Validation response
    API->>API: Store DSC CR in etcd

    API->>DSCCtrl: Watch notification<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token
    DSCCtrl->>API: GET DataScienceCluster<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token

    Note over DSCCtrl,CompCtrl: Component Deployment

    DSCCtrl->>API: CREATE Dashboard CR<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token
    DSCCtrl->>API: CREATE KServe CR<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token
    DSCCtrl->>API: CREATE Ray CR<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token

    API->>CompCtrl: Watch notifications
    CompCtrl->>API: GET Component CRs
    CompCtrl->>API: CREATE Deployments, Services, etc.<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token

    API->>K8s: Schedule pods
    K8s->>K8s: Pull images from registries<br/>Auth: Pull Secret

    Note over Admin,K8s: Flow 2: Metrics Collection

    Prometheus->>API: GET ServiceMonitor resources<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token
    Prometheus->>Metrics: GET /metrics<br/>Auth: Bearer Token (via kube-rbac-proxy)
    Metrics-->>Prometheus: Prometheus metrics

    OpenShiftPrometheus->>Prometheus: Federation scrape<br/>9091/TCP HTTPS<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token
